==English==
===Noun===
'''specific name'''
#{{zoology}} The second word in the [[scientific name]] of a [[species]], following the name of the [[genus]]. This applies only to formal names of animals. Not to be confused with the species name, i.e the name of a species.
::''In the scientific name of the lion ('''Panthera leo''') the specific name is '''leo''', while the species name is '''Panthera leo'''.''
 
